commit.title: [ssr] extended intro patterns: (|) /2/ /2=
commit.message:
[ssr] extended intro patterns: (|) /2/ /2=

Dispatch "=> ( | )"
  this is like [|] but does not perform case (never: no ssr exceptions)

Custom simpl-switch "=> /2/ /3= /4/5="
  /$n/ maps to "ssrdone$n" while /n= maps to "ssrsimpl$n"
  "ssrdone0" is taken by ssreflect (like done, but without split)
